en_637015_0	Major General Nevil Weerasinghe of Sri Lanka Engineers on Monday (4) assumed office as the 29th Adjutant General (AG) of the Sri Lanka Army at his office in the Army Headquarters.
en_637015_1	He succeeded Major General Athula Kodippili.
en_637015_2	Amid religious observances, the new Adjutant General signified the acceptance of his office by leaving his signature for an official document.
en_637015_3	Prior to this appointment, he was serving as the General Officer Commanding, 22 Division in Trincomalee.
en_637015_4	Senior officers, including Colonel AG and staff officers of the Branch were associated with the inauguration of the new office.
